    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1975-05-28T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1975-05-28T12:00:00-05:00" n="231"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d231">
                <head>231. Telegram 123634 From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss>
                    to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Sudan</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d231fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Policy Files, 1975. Confidential.
                        Drafted by Daniel Waterman in <gloss target="#t_AFE1">AF/E</gloss>, cleared
                        in <gloss target="#t_NEA1">NEA</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_S1">S</gloss>/CCT,
                            <gloss target="#t_AFE1">AF/E</gloss>, H, and <persName corresp="#p_DNM1"
                            >Davis</persName>, approved by <persName corresp="#p_SJJ1"
                            >Sisco</persName>
                    </note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d231fn2">The Department informed the Embassy
                        that it had decided to authorize normal EX-IM Bank and <gloss
                            target="#t_OPIC1">OPIC</gloss> transactions.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1975-05-28T17:00:00+00:00">May 28, 1975, 1700Z</date>
                </dateline>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>Subject:</head>
                    <item>Amendment of US Policy Toward Sudan</item>
                </list>
                <list type="references">
                    <head>Ref:</head>
                    <item>Khartoum 1256 and 965</item>
                </list>
                <p>1. Dept. has reviewed <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> policy guidelines
                    toward Sudan and has decided to authorize at this time normal Ex-Im bank and
                        <gloss target="#t_OPIC1">OPIC</gloss> transactions involving Sudan.</p>
                <p>2. Assuming continued satisfactory evolution of relations, we would then be
                    prepaared to consider additional steps toward normalization.</p>
                <p>3. Ambassador may inform <gloss target="#t_GOS1">GOS</gloss> in low-key
                    matter-of-fact manner of <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> decision to
                    authorize <gloss target="#t_EXIM1">ExIm</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_OPIC1"
                        >OPIC</gloss> transactions with Sudan. Under Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_SJJ1">Sisco</persName> informed Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="#p_DFM2">Deng</persName> of policy change.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_IRS1">Ingersoll</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
